                                Parents, Students, & Community Members,

You can check back on this page at anytime to find the newest information released by the school district regarding the school closure and other important student information during this unprecedented time.


If your student needs a device at home to access educational content, please visit our "Request a Device" page.

Students, please continue to check your school district email address.




April 20, 2020 Update - See the Continuity of Learning Plan Approval Letter from Mr. Fisher or the document on the below for information regarding the instuctional plan instruction 2019-2020 school year. You can also view the entire Continuity of Learning Plan.


Food Service during this school closure is Open! Please visit the "Free Lunch Information" page to the left.


The District has plenty of enrichment learning opportunities! Please visit the "Home Learning Resources" page to the left for learing resources while students are at home.


We understand this time can be difficult. We have attached some helpful information regarding Student Wellness during COVID-19. Please visit the document center below label "Support".


Our Playgrounds are closed during this time. This is a reminder regarding Governor Whitmer's "Stay Home-Stay Safe" order. Please know that our school buildings and our school grounds are closed during this state mandate. This directive is for the safety and well-being of all community members. The purpose of this directive is to reduce incidents of COVID-19 infection. Community members should adhere to this very important guidance. Please note that playground equipment on school sites is not to be used at this time.



At Home Learning Resources for Students are available.
Please visit the "Home Learning Resources" page to the left. 

Please check back frequently for updates

                                







